$ Python: doctest
@ doctest

`doctest` finds code-examples in a module's docstrings and executes those, tyipcally for → development/testing purposes.

{ Simple demonstration

  The following simple → development/languages/Python/module is supposed to demonstrate how `doctest`
  could be used.

  gh|about-Python|/standard-library/doctest/theModule.py||

}

sa:

  The → development/languages/Python/standard-library/unittest[`unittest`] module is a bit more elaborate and modelled after → development/languages/Java and SmallTalk testing frameworks.

